        <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Hd1e108">Rubrica 1</head>
        <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Hd1e111" type="question-title">De amore et dilectione</head>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-d1e114">
          <!--98.xml-->
          <cb ed="#V" n="b"/>
          <lb ed="#V" n="46"/>Tertius liber secunde partis
          <lb ed="#V" n="47"/>tractat de dilectione et 
          amici<lb ed="#V" n="48" break="no"/>tia sub his titulis.
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-d1e127">
          <lb ed="#V" n="49"/>
          ¶ De amore et dilectione.
          <lb ed="#V" n="50"/>Rubrica prima. 
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-d1e134">
          <lb ed="#V" n="51"/>
          ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Rd1e131">Salomon in cantico 
            can<lb ed="#V" n="52" break="no"/>ticorum circa fi.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Qd1e138">Fortis est vt
              <lb ed="#V" n="53"/>mors dilectio dura sicut inferus mulatio.
              <lb ed="#V" n="54"/>Aque multe non poterunt extinguere 
              chari<lb ed="#V" n="55" break="no"/>tatem: nec flumina obruent illam. Si dederit
              <lb ed="#V" n="56"/>homo omnem substantiam domus sue pro <sic>
                dilecti<lb ed="#V" n="57" break="no"/>ne</sic>quasi nihil despiciet eum.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-d1e156">
          <lb ed="#V" n="58"/>
          ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Rd1e158">Aristoteles ethicorum libro 4. c. i.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Qd1e160">Omnes diligunt
            <lb ed="#V" n="59"/>magis sua opera vt parentes et poete.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-d1e166"> /
          <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Rd1e168">Li.
            <lb ed="#V" n="60"/>10. et fi. c. 5.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Qd1e168">Unusquisque circa hec: et in his
              <lb ed="#V" n="61"/>operatur que maxime diligit.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-d1e176"> /
          <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Rd1e181">Idem 
            iconomi<lb ed="#V" n="62" break="no"/>rorum lib. i.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Qd1e178">Dissimilitudines morum nequiqui: 
              amabi<lb ed="#V" n="63" break="no"/>les.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-d1e186"> /
          <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Rd1e194">Idem magnorum moralium li. 2. c. 79</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Qd1e188">
            Mul<lb ed="#V" n="64" break="no"/>tis multotiens aut auidere aut abaudire 
            ali<lb ed="#V" n="65" break="no"/>quid de aliquo bono beniuoli simus. <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Rd1e202">Idem
              <lb ed="#V" n="66"/>retho. li. i. c. 10.</ref> Diligere delectabile est. 
            Dili<lb ed="#V" n="67" break="no"/>gi: delectabile est. / <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Rd1e209">Li. 2 c. 6.</ref> Nullus que
            <lb ed="#V" n="68"/>timet amat.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-d1e202"> /
          <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Rd1e218">21. c.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Qd1e204">Non oportet amare 
            tam<lb ed="#V" n="69" break="no"/>que oditurum: sed magis odire tanquam amaturum.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-d1e210">
          <lb ed="#V" n="70"/>
          ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Rd1e230">Iesus filius sirach in eccl. c. 3.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Qd1e214">Omne animal 
            di<lb ed="#V" n="71" break="no"/>ligit similem: sic et omnis homo proximum sibi.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-d1e221"> /
          <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Rd1e241">33. c.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Qd1e223">Si
            <lb ed="#V" n="72"/>est tibi seruus fidelis: sit tibi quasi anima tua.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-d1e229">
          <lb ed="#V" n="73"/>
          ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Rd1e253">Terentius in hecyra. c. 9.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Qd1e233">Qui amat cui odio
            <lb ed="#V" n="74"/>ipse est: bis facere stulte dico: laborem inanem
            <lb ed="#V" n="75"/>ipsius capit: et illi molestiam affert.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-d1e241">
          <lb ed="#V" n="76"/>¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Rd1e267" corresp="bHY6yh-d27579-Qd1e245">Tullius de officiis: li. 2. c. 7.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Qd1e245" source="http://scta.info/resource/gpza5l-7tvweq-d1e179@1-18">Omnium 
            re<lb ed="#V" n="77" break="no"/>rum nec aptius est quicquam ad opes tuendas
            <lb ed="#V" n="78"/>ac tenendas qua diligi: nec alienius quam timeri</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-d1e253">
          <lb ed="#V" n="79"/>
          <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Rd1e281">11. cap.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Qd1e257">Uehemeter multitudinis amor
            <lb ed="#V" n="80"/>commouetur ipsa fama et opinione 
            libera<lb ed="#V" n="81" break="no"/>litatis beniuolentie iustitie fidei 
            omnium<lb ed="#V" n="82" break="no"/>que earum virtutum que pertinent ad 
            man<lb ed="#V" n="83" break="no"/>suetudinem morum ac felicitatem.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-d1e269">
          <lb ed="#V" n="84"/>
          <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Qd1e273">/ Idem de amicitia: Nihil est virtute 
            ama<lb ed="#V" n="85" break="no"/>bilius. Nihil quod magis alliceat ad 
            dili<lb ed="#V" n="86" break="no"/>gendum. Quippe cum virtute et probitate:
            <lb ed="#V" n="87"/>etiam eos quos nunquam vidimus 
            quod<lb ed="#V" n="88" break="no"/>dammodo diligamus. Confirmatur 
            a<lb ed="#V" n="89" break="no"/>mor ex beneficio accepio et studio 
            per<lb ed="#V" n="90" break="no"/>specto: et consuetudine adiuncia.<!--99.xml-->
            <pb ed="#V" n="36-v"/>
            <cb ed="#V" n="a"/>
          </quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-d1e296">
          <lb ed="#V" n="1"/>
          <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Rd1e326">Idem de fine bonorum et malorum li. 5.
            <lb ed="#V" n="2"/>et fi.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Qd1e300">Omne animal seipsum diligit.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-d1e307"> 
          <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Rd1e338">Idem de 
            le<lb ed="#V" n="3" break="no"/>gibus li. i.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Qd1e309">Natura propensi sumus ad 
              diligen<lb ed="#V" n="4" break="no"/>dos homines quod fundamentum iuris est.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-d1e317"> /
          <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Rd1e351">Idem
            <lb ed="#V" n="5"/>de natura deorum li. i.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Qd1e319">Causarum ipsum 
              ver<lb ed="#V" n="6" break="no"/>bum est amoris.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-d1e327">
          <lb ed="#V" n="7"/>
          ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Rd1e366">Ouidius de arte amandi li. 2.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Qd1e331">Sit procul
            <lb ed="#V" n="8"/>omne nephas: vt amaris amabilis esto.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-d1e337"> /
          <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Qd1e339">Erue
            <lb ed="#V" n="9"/>fastus. Curam mansuri quisquis amoris habes
            <lb ed="#V" n="10"/>Dulcibus est verbis: mollis eliciendus amor
            <lb ed="#V" n="11"/>Uane scitque absens: et nouus intrat amor.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-d1e349">
          <lb ed="#V" n="12"/>
          ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Rd1e390">Mattheus in euangel. c. 6.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Qd1e353">Ubi thesaurus
            <lb ed="#V" n="13"/>tuus: ibi et cor tuum.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-d1e359">
          <lb ed="#V" n="14"/>
          ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Rd1e402">Ioannes in euange. c. 15.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Qd1e363">Maiorem hac 
            dile<lb ed="#V" n="15" break="no"/>ctionem nemo habet: vt animam suam quis ponat
            <lb ed="#V" n="16"/>pro amicis suis. / <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Rd1e410">Idem apostolus in euange. in epistola
              <lb ed="#V" n="17"/>i. c. 3.</ref>Non diligamus verba neque lingua:
            <lb ed="#V" n="18"/>sed opere et veritate.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-d1e376"> /
          <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Rd1e422">4. c.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Qd1e378">Timor non est in
            <lb ed="#V" n="19"/>charitate: sed perfecta charitas foris mittit
            <lb ed="#V" n="20"/>timorem.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-d1e386">
          <lb ed="#V" n="21"/>
          ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Rd1e436">Seneca epistolarum ad lucillum li. 2. e. i.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Qd1e390">Si
            <lb ed="#V" n="22"/>vis amari: ama.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-d1e396"> /
          <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Rd1e446">Li. 4. c. 8. et fi.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Qd1e398">Conciliari
            <lb ed="#V" n="23"/>non nisi turpi ratione amor turpium potest.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-d1e404">
          <lb ed="#V" n="24"/>
          / <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Rd1e458">Lib. 6. e. 5.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Qd1e408">Qui colitur et amatur. Non 
            po<lb ed="#V" n="25" break="no"/>test amor cum timore misceri.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-d1e414"> /
          <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Rd1e468">Idem 
            de<lb ed="#V" n="26" break="no"/>clam. li. 8 causa. 6. et fi.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Qd1e416">Magnus est amor qui
              <lb ed="#V" n="27"/>ex misericordia venit.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-d1e424">
          <lb ed="#V" n="28"/>
          ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Rd1e483">Iuuenalis li. i. satis 3.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Qd1e428">Quis nunc diligitur nisi
            <lb ed="#V" n="29"/>conscius et cui feruens. Estuat occultis 
            ani<lb ed="#V" n="30" break="no"/>mus semperque tacendis.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-d1e437">
          <lb ed="#V" n="31"/>
          ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Rd1e498">Lex diges. ti. de donationibus inter virum
            <lb ed="#V" n="32"/>et vxo. li. 3. in prin.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Qd1e441">Amor honestus solis 
              ani<lb ed="#V" n="33" break="no"/>mis existimatur.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-d1e449">
          <lb ed="#V" n="34"/>
          ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Rd1e513">Martialis cocus li. vndique suscepto. c. 2.</ref>
          <lb ed="#V" n="35"/><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Qd1e453">Miraris quod nullus amet te ceciliane.
            <lb ed="#V" n="36"/>Non quod amas nullum: dilige carus eris.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-d1e461">
          <lb ed="#V" n="37"/>
          <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Rd1e526">c. 4.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Qd1e465">Nulli carus erat erodinus et sibi nullus.
            <lb ed="#V" n="38"/>Conuentus morum faculam succendit amoris.
            <lb ed="#V" n="39"/>Moribus at variis gratia distrahitur.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-d1e473"> /
          <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Rd1e538">Cap. 5</ref>
          <lb ed="#V" n="40"/><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Qd1e475">Inuitus nemo: nemo coactus amat.
            <lb ed="#V" n="41"/>Blandiciis non imperio vis crescit amoris.
            <lb ed="#V" n="42"/>Dilige nos omnes: vt ameris. ab omnibus vnus.
            <lb ed="#V" n="43"/>Querit amor pariles: dissimiles odium.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-d1e487">
          <lb ed="#V" n="44"/>
          <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Rd1e555">c. 6.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Qd1e491">Nescit amor vehemens: ad queque 
            peri<lb ed="#V" n="45" break="no"/>cula rumpi.<!--99.xml-->
            <cb ed="#V" n="b"/>
          </quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-d1e501">
          <lb ed="#V" n="46"/>
          ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Rd1e571">Augustinus in epig. pros. emp. 2.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Qd1e505">Sic 
            dili<lb ed="#V" n="47" break="no"/>gendi sunt homines: vt eorum non diligantur
            <lb ed="#V" n="48"/>errores.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-d1e514">
          <lb ed="#V" n="49"/>
          ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Rd1e586">Boetius de consolatione li. 4. c. 8.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Qd1e518" source="http://scta.info/resource/hy7y6y-d1e75-d1e568@61-66">Omni
            <lb ed="#V" n="50"/>iure bonos: et miser esse malis.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-d1e524"> /
          <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Rd1e596">Idem in
            <lb ed="#V" n="51"/>musica li. i. c. i.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Qd1e526">Amica est similitudo: odiosa 
              dis<lb ed="#V" n="52" break="no"/>similitudo atque contria. Amorem dilectionemque 
              similitu<lb ed="#V" n="53" break="no"/>do conciliat.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-d1e536"> /
          <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Rd1e611">Libro. 2 c. 16. et fi.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Qd1e538">O felix
            <lb ed="#V" n="54"/>hominum genus: Si vestros animos amor
            <lb ed="#V" n="55"/>Quo celum regitur regat.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-d1e546">
          <lb ed="#V" n="56"/>
          ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Rd1e625">Cassiodorus de amicitia. c. i</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Qd1e550">Uix inuenitur
            <lb ed="#V" n="57"/>dilectio: que non sit questuaria et venalis.
            <lb ed="#V" n="58"/><ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Rd1e632">c. 3.</ref>Amor est quedam vis appetitiua rerum:
            <lb ed="#V" n="59"/>quas desiderio eligimus et amplectimur ad
            <lb ed="#V" n="60"/>fruendum. Dilectio exacto animi iudicio vires 
            ca<lb ed="#V" n="61" break="no"/>pit.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-d1e564"> /
          <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Rd1e644">c. 26 et fi.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Qd1e566">Dilectionis est consulere et
            <lb ed="#V" n="62"/>amico beneficia exhibere.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-d1e572">
          <lb ed="#V" n="63"/>
          ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Rd1e656">Uersificator fabularum esopi. 28 fa.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Qd1e576">
            Nul<lb ed="#V" n="64" break="no"/>lus amor durat: nisi fructus seruet amorem.
            <lb ed="#V" n="65"/>Quilibet est tanti: munera quanta facit.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-d1e585">
          <lb ed="#V" n="66"/>
          ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Rd1e671">Auctor li. qui dicitur pamphilus. c. 3.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Qd1e589">
            Exci<lb ed="#V" n="67" break="no"/>tat et nutrit facundia dulcis amor.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-d1e595">
          <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Rd1e681">c. 13</ref>
          <lb ed="#V" n="68"/><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d27579-Qd1e597">Usu crescit amor omnis: decrescit et vsu.
            <lb ed="#V" n="69"/>Omnis et impastus: attenuatur amor.</quote>
        </p>
      </div>
